The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	Vishnu Vardhan, the eighth seed, beat I-Ta Chen of Taipei 6-1, 6-0 at the Oil-India ITF Mens Futures tennis tournament at the Jaidip Mukerjea Tennis Academy on Tuesday. Fifth seed Divij Sharan defeated qualifier Gilard Berman of Israel 6-4, 6-4. Top seed Benjamin Balleret of Monaco was leading 6-0, 4-0 against Vaja Uzakov of Uzbekistan when the latter retired. In mens doubles, local lad Saurav Panja and Saurav Sukul lost to the second seeded pair of Alexei Filenkov of Russia and Peter Steinberger of Germany 7-6, 6-4.          
	 Olympic gold medallist Abhinav Bindra will be honoured by the Calcutta Sports Journalists Club with the Best Sportsperson of the Year Award in its annual awards ceremony to be held at the Asutosh Birth Centenary Hall on Saturday. Mountaineer Bachendri Pal and former India hockey player Ashok Kumar will also be awarded with the Lifetime Achievement Awards. Junior paddler Ankita Das will receive the Best Junior Sportsperson of the Year award.      
	List of Awardees      
	Archery: Somnath Mondal; Athletics: Sushmita Singha Roy; Basketball: Arundhaty Banerjee; Badminton: Rituparna Das; Chess: Surya Sekhar Ganguly; Cricket: Wriddhiman Saha (men), Priyanka Roy (women); Football: Sunil Chetri; Hockey: Imran Khan; Kabaddi: Jyotish Biswas; Swimming: Ronit Dey; Sports organiser: Swapan Kumar Raha; Table tennis: Saurav Chakraborty; Tennis: Treta Bhattacharya.          
	 Don Bosco beat Birla High School by nine wickets in the under-16 Inter School cricket tournament organised by Sloba Cricket Coaching Camp at St Lawrence School Ground on Tuesday.      
	BRIEF SCORES: Birla High School 182/6 (Saif Akhtar 76). Don Bosco School 185/1 (Adrish Saha 91 n.o.) Don Bosco School won by 9 wkts.                
